Introduction

Purpose of this Project:

  • This project is designed to visualize the effects of the Economic Status of a State on the Life and Death of its Residents from year 2000 to year 2012
  • Primarily, the Average Life Expectancy and the GDP per Capita of both Sex are compared to show the conditions of Countries in comparison with each other.

Conclusion

Takeaways

  • Strong correlation between Life Expectancy and GDP per Capita
  • High Income Groups Tend to have lower GINI coefficients and hence lower income gaps
  • Primary Cause of Mortality in Low Income Groups are Communicable Diseases
  • Over time, the economic conditions of countries grow better (significant in Low Income Regions)
  • As countries grow economically, Cancer and Cardiovascular Diseases rise significantly and then decrease
